<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-08-04T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-08-04T16:00:00-05:00" n="134" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d134">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51 W 89 Italy/9: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Child</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-08-04T17:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">August 4,
                                        1922—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>117. Your 126, July 27, 1 p.m.</p>
                        <p>Please inform Foreign Office that the most opportune time for arrival
                            Italian delegates at Washington would be about the middle of October,
                                1922.<note n="31" xml:id="d134fn31">The Italian Government did not
                                open negotiations with the World War Foreign Debt Commission until
                                1925; see <hi rend="italic">Combined Annual Reports of the World War
                                    Foreign Debt Commission</hi>, 1922–1926 (Washington, Government
                                Printing Office, 1927), pp. 14, 27, 48–50.</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>